# Video encoding in linux / OSX.

## Nice looking videos that are compressed using h264 codecc:

    ffmpeg -i input.mov -c:v h264 output.mp4

Add `-an` to remove the audio.

## OSX presentation video encoding:

For videos to work in presentations on OSX, use motion jpeg encoding for AVI files.

    ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -f avi -c:v mjpeg output.avi

NOTE: In some versions of Ubuntu, use 'avconv' instead of 'ffmpeg'.
